- run tls-cert-req.sh and upload the $HOST.csr file at:

    https://ca.corp.redhat.com/ca/ee/ca/profileSelect?profileId=caServerCert

- wait for an e-mail with subject "Your Certificate Request"
- open the e-mail and click the "URL" link inside
- download the base64-encoded server certificate as $HOST.crt
- download the base64-encoded CA certificate in PKCS7 format as $HOST-ca.pk7
- transform it to the X509 format:

    openssl pkcs7 -print_certs -in $HOST-ca.pk7 -out $HOST-ca.crt
